================================================================================
Notes on the LGPL-licensed dependencies (libpoly, GMP, MPFR)
================================================================================

These libraries are LGPL. Xolver as a whole is Apache 2.0, which is compatible
with LGPL-licensed libraries when used as dynamically-linked or statically-
linked libraries, provided that:

  - the LGPL libraries' source code remains accessible to recipients
    (satisfied: libpoly is a public git submodule pointing at the upstream
     repository; GMP and MPFR are public packages from gmplib.org / mpfr.org)
  - users are able to relink Xolver against a modified version of the LGPL
    library (satisfied by Xolver's open build system: rebuild from source with
    a different libpoly / GMP / MPFR is documented in README.md)

For binary distributions, the original source of each LGPL library is
reachable via the URLs above.
